<reference id="api_onscenetokenwillexpire">
    <title><ph keyref="OnSceneTokenWillExpire"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">Occurs when the scene token expires in 30 seconds.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm keyref="OnSceneTokenWillExpire"/>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody>
        <section id="prototype">
            <p outputclass="codeblock">
                <codeblock props="android" outputclass="language-java"/>
                <codeblock props="ios mac" outputclass="language-objectivec"/>
                <codeblock props="windows" outputclass="language-cpp">virtual void OnSceneTokenWillExpire(const std::string&amp; scene_id,
                    const std::string&amp; token) = 0;</codeblock>
                <codeblock props="electron" outputclass="language-typescript"/>
                <codeblock props="unity" outputclass="language-csharp"/>
                <codeblock props="rn" outputclass="language-typescript"/>
                <codeblock props="flutter" outputclass="language-dart"/>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc">
            <dl outputclass="since">
                <dlentry>
                    <dt>Since</dt>
                    <dd>v</dd>
                </dlentry>
            </dl>
            <p>The user becomes offline if the scene token used in the <xref keyref="Join"/> method expires. The SDK triggers this callback 30 seconds before the scene token expires to remind the application to get a new token. Upon receiving this callback, generate a new token on the server and call the <xref keyref="RenewSceneToken"/> method to pass the new scene token to the SDK.</p>
            <note>If the scene gets disconnected because of token expiration, the SDK can still
                publish streams before you call <xref keyref="Leave"/> to leave the scene.</note>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters"><title>Parameters</title>
            <parml>
                <plentry>
                    <pt>scene_id</pt>
                    <pd>The scene ID.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry>
                    <pt>token</pt>
                    <pd>The scene token that expires in 30 seconds.</pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>
